1. What is an Exception?

An exception is an unwanted event that occurs during program execution, stopping the normal flow.

Example: division by zero, array index out of bounds, null pointer, file not found.


LIST OF ALL
üìå CHECKED (COMPILE-TIME) EXCEPTIONS ‚Äî FULL LIST (MOST COMMON)

Compiler forces handling.

‚úî From java.io

IOException

